This paper deals with the optimization of energy purchase and wireless load sharing in cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a repeated Nash bargaining scheme for energy cost sharing, which involves game theory and optimization, making it relevant to the sub-category of game theory and decision making (cs.GT). The paper also involves the optimization of energy consumption, which is related to control engineering (cs.SY) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper deals with the joint optimization of day-ahead and real-time energy purchase, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
